race.comment: THE PENSKE FILE (4) is in red-hot form, scoring in his last two. Only missed the frame once at this venue and looks set for the rise to 2000m. Will take plenty of beating. ECLIPSION (3) returned to somewhere near his best form last start at Cairns when giving his backers a bold sight. Rises sharply in trip but keeps the service of gun hoop in Wiggins. Expect him to charge forward again and take some reeling in. FINAL COMMENT (5) failed in his stable debut at Emerald but his form lines down south read very well for this. Takes some forgiving but is worth it. DIASONIC (6) doesn't win very often but ran a nice race last time out here when a narrow second. Peak fitness now and has form over this journey. Certainly in the mix. TORQUE ESPAGNA (7) hasn't struck through for a long time but has been knocking on the door. Could sneak into the frame.
